org.middleheaven.util.collections
Class Range<T,I>

java.lang.Object
  org.middleheaven.util.collections.AbstractEnumerable<T>
      org.middleheaven.util.collections.Range<T,I>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of the value in the range.
I - type of the incremente. Normally is the same as T, but not allways( i.e. dates have increment as integers)
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<T>, Enumerable<T>, RandomEnumerable<T>
public class Range<T,I>
extends AbstractEnumerable<T>
implements RandomEnumerable<T>

Provides range semantics and operations. A Range is like an Interval with iterator semantics over the interval values. An Incrementor is used to define how the iteration visits the values in the interval.

union

public Range<T,I> union(Interval<T> other)
The union of this range with an another. The result is a range from the lowest start to the greatest end Note that union is a commutative operation, meaning that R.union(T).equals(T.union(R)) == true , R and T being instances of Range.

Parameters:
other -
Returns:
a range from the lowest start to the greatest end. Example : [2,3] merged with [7,10] will return [2,10]
